eval("__webpack_require__.r(__webpack_exports__);\n/* harmony export */ __webpack_require__.d(__webpack_exports__, {\n/* harmony export */   POSTS: () => (/* binding */ POSTS),\n/* harmony export */   getPostBySlug: () => (/* binding */ getPostBySlug)\n/* harmony export */ });\nconst POSTS = [\n    {\n        slug: \"how-to-choose-a-printing-company-in-lagos\",\n        title: \"How to Choose a Printing Company in Lagos Without Regrets\",\n        excerpt: \"A practical guide to help you avoid costly mistakes when choosing a printing press in Lagos. From quality checks to turnaround time, here is what really matters.\",\n        date: \"May 20, 2026\",\n        category: \"Business Tips\",\n        readTime: \"5 min read\",\n        featured: true,\n        thumbnail: \"/printing-machine.png\",\n        content: `\r\nChoosing a printing company in Lagos is not something most people think about until something goes wrong. A batch of business cards with the wrong colours. Branded bags that fall apart after one use. Flyers delivered two days after your event. These are real stories that happen every week to businesses across Ogba, Ikeja, and the rest of Lagos.\r\n\r\nThis guide will help you ask the right questions so you choose a printing company you can actually trust.\r\n\r\n## 1. Look at Real Work, Not Just Promises\r\n\r\nAny printing company can promise high quality. What matters is what they have actually delivered. Before you place an order, ask to see physical samples not just photos on a website. Ask specifically for samples of the product you need. If you want branded bags, ask to see branded bags they have produced before. If you want business cards, hold one in your hand and feel the weight, check the colour accuracy, and look for sharp clean edges.\r\n\r\nAt ESTOB Prints, we have over 25 years of physical work you can inspect. We produce everything from premium business cards and corporate stationery to large format banners and branded merchandise and we stand behind every single piece we produce.\r\n\r\n## 2. Verify Their Equipment and Production Process\r\n\r\nThe quality of your print job is directly tied to the machines being used. Modern offset printing presses produce sharper, more consistent results than outdated equipment. Digital printers have their place, but for large volumes and brand critical work, offset printing delivers superior colour accuracy and finish.\r\n\r\nDo not be afraid to ask a printing company what equipment they use. A serious print house will be happy to answer. A print shop that cannot give you a clear answer is one to approach with caution.\r\n\r\n## 3. Confirm Turnaround Time Before You Pay\r\n\r\nDeadlines matter. Whether you are printing materials for a product launch, a church anniversary, a corporate event, or a wedding, your printer must be able to commit to a delivery date and actually meet it.\r\n\r\nAlways confirm turnaround time before you pay. Get it confirmed in writing if possible. And factor in time for revisions. A professional printing company will allow for at least one round of proof review before final production begins.\r\n\r\n## 4. Understand What You Are Paying For\r\n\r\nPricing in the Lagos printing market varies widely and the difference is almost always quality. A significantly lower price usually means cheaper materials, older equipment, or corners cut on finishing and colour accuracy.\r\n\r\nWhen you receive a quote, ask what is included. Does it cover design? Does it include lamination or finishing? Is delivery part of the price or charged separately?\r\n\r\nAt ESTOB Prints, we offer transparent, competitive pricing with no hidden charges. What we quote is what you pay and what you receive will always reflect the standard your brand deserves.\r\n\r\n## 5. Visit Their Physical Location\r\n\r\nA printing company with a physical address gives you accountability. You can visit before placing your order, inspect work in progress, and build a genuine long term relationship. A company with no physical presence offers little recourse if something goes wrong.\r\n\r\nESTOB Prints operates from two locations in Lagos. Our main office is at 1 Akinwale Street, Off Yaya Abatan, Ogba, Ikeja. Our second location is at 56 Ijaiye Road, Agege, Lagos. Walk in anytime and speak with our team directly.\r\n\r\n## 6. Look for a Full Service Print Partner\r\n\r\nA printing company that offers a full range of services is more valuable than one that only does one thing. As your business grows, your print needs will evolve. You may start with business cards, then need branded bags, then large format banners, then corporate merchandise for a major event.\r\n\r\nESTOB Prints covers all of this under one roof. Premium printing, branding and corporate identity, corporate merchandise, large format printing, promotional materials, custom print solutions, and offset paper supplies. You build one relationship and it serves you at every stage of your growth.\r\n\r\nIf you are also thinking about corporate gifting, read our article on [why branded bags are the best corporate gift in Nigeria](/Insights/why-branded-bags-are-the-best-corporate-gift) to see how a great print partner can help you leave a lasting impression.\r\n\r\n## Final Thought\r\n\r\nThe right printing company is one that treats your brand with the same seriousness you do. One that asks the right questions, gives honest advice, meets deadlines, and delivers work that makes you proud to hand it to your clients.\r\n\r\nThat is exactly what ESTOB Prints has been doing for businesses, churches, organizations, and events across Lagos and Nigeria for over 25 years. [Chat with us on WhatsApp](https://wa.me/2349074130380) today and let us show you what great printing looks like.\r\n    `\n    },\n    {\n        slug: \"why-branded-bags-are-the-best-corporate-gift\",\n        title: \"Why Branded Bags Are the Best Corporate Gift in Nigeria\",\n        excerpt: \"Corporate gifts say a lot about your brand. Branded bags are one of the most effective, long lasting, and visible gifts you can give clients, staff, and event guests in Nigeria.\",\n        date: \"May 15, 2026\",\n        category: \"Branding\",\n        readTime: \"4 min read\",\n        thumbnail: \"/hair-bag.jpg\",\n        content: `\r\nCorporate gifting is one of the most powerful tools available to businesses in Nigeria when done right. The wrong gift says we picked the cheapest option. The right gift says we value this relationship. And in Nigeria's competitive business landscape, that distinction matters enormously.\r\n\r\nBranded bags, when produced at a premium level, consistently outperform every other corporate gift category. Here is why.\r\n\r\n## They Are Used Every Single Day\r\n\r\nUnlike branded pens that run out of ink or wall calendars that get forgotten, a quality branded bag becomes part of your recipient's daily routine. It goes to the market. It goes to the office. It goes to school runs, gym sessions, and weekend trips. Every single trip is a brand impression at no additional cost to you.\r\n\r\nThink about what that means over the life of one bag. A bag used three times a week for a year delivers over 150 brand impressions. That is sustained, physical visibility that is very difficult to replicate through any other channel.\r\n\r\n## They Travel Everywhere Your Clients Go\r\n\r\nWhen your client carries your branded bag through Lekki, Ikeja, Abuja, or Port Harcourt, they are promoting your business to everyone who sees them. This is organic, word of mouth marketing that money cannot easily replicate.\r\n\r\nThe reach of a well designed branded bag extends far beyond the original recipient. People notice quality. They ask questions. And often, the next client you gain will be someone who simply asked where did you get that bag.\r\n\r\n## They Signal Premium Quality\r\n\r\nThe gift you give reflects the standard of your business. A beautifully crafted branded bag communicates permanence, quality, and attention to detail. Exactly the qualities you want associated with your brand.\r\n\r\nAt ESTOB Prints, we produce branded bags across a full range of styles, materials, and sizes. From lightweight paper bags to premium boxed packaging, every bag we produce is crafted to represent your brand at its absolute best.\r\n\r\n## They Are Highly Customisable\r\n\r\nOne of the greatest advantages of branded bags is the level of customisation available. You can specify the material whether paper, non-woven, canvas, or leather effect. You can choose the handle style, the bag size, the print finish, and even the internal lining. The result is a product that feels completely unique to your brand.\r\n\r\nOur team at ESTOB Prints works with clients from initial concept through to final delivery, ensuring every detail of your branded bag reflects your brand identity accurately and beautifully.\r\n\r\n## They Last Long and Keep Working\r\n\r\nA quality branded bag can last for years. That means years of brand visibility from a single investment. This is particularly valuable for Nigerian businesses operating in sectors where brand trust is everything. Financial services, healthcare, hospitality, fashion, and professional services all benefit enormously from this kind of long term brand presence.\r\n\r\n## Who Should Use Branded Bags?\r\n\r\nBranded bags work across virtually every business category. We produce them for corporate organizations distributing gifts at annual general meetings, for fashion and beauty brands packaging their products, for churches distributing anniversary souvenirs, for event planners sourcing guest gifts, and for government agencies marking official occasions.\r\n\r\nIf you want to understand the full picture of what makes a great print partner, read our guide on [how to choose a printing company in Lagos](/Insights/how-to-choose-a-printing-company-in-lagos) before placing your next order.\r\n\r\n## Ready to Order?\r\n\r\nWhether you need 50 bags for a product launch or 5,000 for a national corporate event, ESTOB Prints delivers premium branded bags with fast turnaround across Lagos and Nigeria. [Send us a message on WhatsApp](https://wa.me/2349074130380) today and let our team help you create something your recipients will actually use and value.\r\n    `\n    },\n    {\n        slug: \"art-paper-vs-matt-paper\",\n        title: \"Art Paper vs Matte Paper: Which One Should You Choose?\",\n        excerpt: \"Choosing the wrong paper can ruin an otherwise perfect print job. Here is a clear, simple breakdown of art paper vs matte paper and when to use each one.\",\n        date: \"May 10, 2026\",\n        category: \"Print Tips\",\n        readTime: \"4 min read\",\n        thumbnail: \"/Matte-paper.png\",\n        content: `\r\nOne of the most common questions we receive at ESTOB Prints is this: what is the difference between art paper and matte paper? It seems like a small detail but choosing the wrong paper can significantly affect how your final print looks, feels, and communicates to your audience.\r\n\r\nThis guide breaks it down simply so you can make the right choice every time.\r\n\r\n## What Is Art Paper?\r\n\r\nArt paper also called glossy paper has a shiny, coated surface that reflects light. This reflective quality makes colours appear more vibrant and images look sharper and more detailed. Art paper is the finish you see on magazine covers, product catalogues, and high impact flyers.\r\n\r\nArt paper works best for product catalogues and lookbooks, marketing flyers and promotional materials, brochures where visual impact is the priority, posters and large format print, and any material where you want colours to feel bold and vivid.\r\n\r\nThe one tradeoff with art paper is that the glossy surface can show fingerprints and smudges easily. It is also harder to write on, which makes it less suitable for materials your audience needs to annotate or fill in.\r\n\r\n## What Is Matte Paper?\r\n\r\nMatte paper has a smooth, non reflective finish. It does not shine or reflect light, which gives it a calmer, more sophisticated appearance. Many people describe matte paper as feeling more premium in the hand. There is a tactile quality to it that glossy paper does not replicate.\r\n\r\nMatte paper works best for business cards and corporate stationery, high end brochures and company profiles, books, reports, and annual reviews, presentation folders, and any material that will be read for a long time or handled repeatedly.\r\n\r\nThe advantage of matte paper is that it is comfortable on the eyes for extended reading and does not attract fingerprints the way glossy paper does. It also takes pen and pencil marks well, making it ideal for materials that need to be filled in or annotated.\r\n\r\n## Which One Should You Choose?\r\n\r\nThe simplest way to decide is to ask yourself one question: Is this material meant to impress visually, or is it meant to be read and used?\r\n\r\nIf your print material is primarily a visual showcase such as a product flyer, a catalogue, or a poster, art paper will make your images and colours pop.\r\n\r\nIf your print material is primarily a document or reference such as a business card, a company profile, a corporate brochure, or a report, matte paper will feel more professional and be more comfortable to read and handle.\r\n\r\n## What About Paper Weight?\r\n\r\nPaper weight matters just as much as finish. Both art paper and matte paper come in a range of weights measured in grams per square metre. As a general guide, 90 to 115gsm is standard weight suitable for flyers and internal documents. 130 to 170gsm is medium weight good for brochures and marketing materials. 200 to 300gsm is heavyweight ideal for business cards, covers, and premium stationery. 350gsm and above is board weight used for packaging and premium cards.\r\n\r\nAt ESTOB Prints, we supply both art paper and matte paper in a full range of weights and sizes, sourced directly from trusted international manufacturers. Our team will always advise you on the best combination of finish and weight for your specific project.\r\n\r\n## Offset Paper Supplies in Lagos\r\n\r\nIf you are a printer or a business with high volume paper needs, ESTOB Prints also supplies premium offset paper in bulk including art paper, matte paper, cream bond, and standard offset rolls in 24 and 36 inch sizes. We source directly from international manufacturers and offer competitive pricing with fast delivery across Lagos.\r\n\r\nIf you are still figuring out which print partner is right for you, our guide on [how to choose a printing company in Lagos](/Insights/how-to-choose-a-printing-company-in-lagos) will walk you through everything you need to know.\r\n\r\n## Still Not Sure?\r\n\r\nIf you are unsure which paper type is right for your project, our team at ESTOB Prints is always happy to advise. We have over 25 years of experience helping businesses across Lagos choose the right materials for the right jobs. [Chat with us on WhatsApp](https://wa.me/2349074130380) and let us help you get it right.\r\n    `\n    }\n];\nfunction getPostBySlug(slug) {\n    return POSTS.find((p)=>p.slug === slug);\n}\n//# sourceURL=[module]\n//# sourceMappingURL=data:application/json;charset=utf-8;base64,\n//# sourceURL=webpack-internal:///(ssr)/./src/lib/posts.ts\n");

